First Principles Thinking : When analyzing problems, technical architecture, and code module combinations, adhere to "First Principles Thinking."
Coding Principles : When coding, adhere to the "DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) Principle," "KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid) Principle," "SOLID Principles," and "YAGNI (You Ain't Gonna Need It) Principle."
Code Decomposition : If a single class, function, or code file exceeds 500 lines, identify, decompose, and separate it. During the process of identification, decomposition, and separation, adhere to the principles mentioned above.


